# Seeds for failure cases proptest has generated in the past. It is
# automatically read and these particular cases re-run before any
# novel cases are generated.
#
# Intentionally empty: the STW-091 + STW-088 + STW-094 fixes closed
# the kmeans++ K>N panic (Kmeans++ now duplicates the most-recently-
# picked centroid instead of returning empty centroids on the n<K
# path, so the downstream `step_elkan_slice` Lloyd step's
# `metric.emd(centroid_i, centroid_j)` pairwise-dist loop never
# reaches the empty-support panic at `bins.rs:95`). Properties (a)
# and (b) gained a `prop_assume!(points.iter().any(|h| h.n() > 0))`
# guard so the all-K-centroids-non-empty assertion is only checked
# on inputs that have at least one non-empty histogram; the
# all-empty-input edge case is the degenerate early-return path
# covered by property (c)/(d). With the K>N fix + the prop_assume
# guard, proptest's randomized inputs do not surface any new panic
# site the existing 5 sub-tests + the 5 property sub-tests pin, so
# this file is empty until a future regression reintroduces a
# panic site.
